CHANGELOG.md:338:- Added depth-2 Theramini duet end-to-end test coverage (frac-0119): `tests/test_theramini_duet.py` now declares `depth: 2` in its module docstring and includes `TheraminiDuetEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing Theramini duet surface in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/theramini_duet.py` through one realistic conversation lifecycle. The test builds an active human-gesture state, asserts `normalize_theramini_state(...)` exposes the shared listening contract (`listening`, `speaking=False`, `silence_request=False`, `human_gesture_active`, and a `conversation` payload with `phase="listening"` / `policy="turn_taking"` / `speaker="human"`), confirms `plan_duet_response(...)` for that state produces a listening `ConversationDecision` (`lead_role="theramini"`, `support_role="cypherclaw"`, `max_overlap_beats=0`) and that `should_enter_duet(...)` is `True`, then transitions through a silence-past-response-delay state with `requested_policy="call/response"` to a speaking `ConversationDecision` (`policy="call_response"`, `may_play=True`, `lead_role="cypherclaw"`, non-empty `harmonic_intervals`, `accompaniment_texture="answering_phrase"`, non-empty `response_register` and `rhythmic_sympathy`), checks focused-helper agreement (`suggest_response_key(440.0) == ("A", root>0)`, `suggest_response_register(440.0)` matches the speaking decision's `response_register`, `suggest_response_density(1.0) == "dense"`, `suggest_response_phrase(...)` returns 3-6 positive-frequency / positive-duration notes, and `calculate_wait_beats(0, 0.5) == 0`), then transitions to a long-silence solo state where `plan_duet_response(...)` returns `phase="solo"` / `duet_active=False` and `should_exit_duet(...)` is `True`, asserts `supported_partner_behaviors()` covers the documented ensemble-space behaviors, and round-trips a primitive diagnostic of the listening normalized state, the speaking and solo decision payloads via `ConversationDecision.to_dict()`, the focused helper outputs, and the supported partner behaviors through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_theramini_duet_depth.py` pins the base test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method plus a machine-readable depth marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the Theramini duet surface already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4679 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:368:- Added depth-2 render-seed end-to-end test coverage (frac-0106): `tests/test_render_seed.py` now includes `RenderSeedEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `src/cypherclaw/render/seed.py` public surface through one realistic deterministic-seed lifecycle. The coverage walks a phrase → voice → event family of `seed_path` tuples through `derive_seed(...)` and asserts each sub-seed is in the 32-bit range, deterministic on re-derivation, and unique across the family; re-deriving the same family from a perturbed root seed produces a different sub-seed at every position; the same paths attached to `Event(seed_path=...)` instances preserve the tuple-cast invariant and re-derive to the original sub-seed via `event.seed_path`; and a JSON-safe `{root_seed, alt_root_seed, family: [{event_id, path, seed, alt_seed, event_seed_path}]}` diagnostic round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)` while preserving sub-seed values, event count, and per-position seeds. `tests/test_test_render_seed_depth.py` pins the render-seed test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the seed helper already produced meaningful one-path SHA-256 output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4637 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:372:- Added depth-2 render-events end-to-end test coverage (frac-0104): `tests/test_render_events.py` now includes `RenderEventsEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `src/cypherclaw/render/events.py` public surface through one realistic two-event lifecycle: a non-trivial `SectionEnvelope` is sampled and per-parameter `value_at(...)` agrees with the `SectionEnvelopeSample` for every `SECTION_ENVELOPE_PARAMETERS` channel, a custom `PerformanceIntent` round-trips its declared fields, two `Event` instances (phrase-start `IntentTag.BUILD` and phrase-end / cadential `IntentTag.SETTLE`) populate the full `Event` field surface, `lock_score_fields()` freezes every member of `Event.SCORE_LEVEL_FIELDS` while leaving sensor / timing / `rule_stack` mutable, both events round-trip through `to_json_dict()`/`from_json_dict()`, `to_json()`/`from_json()`, and `to_osc_bundle()`/`from_osc_bundle()` with structural equality and preserved `seed_path` tuples, and a combined diagnostic of `IntentTag` membership, `VALID_ARC_SHAPES`, `SECTION_ENVELOPE_PARAMETERS`, the sampled envelope values, the `PerformanceIntent` snapshot, and both event JSON dicts round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_render_events_depth.py` pins the render-events test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the events module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4631 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:380:- Added depth-2 primary render-path end-to-end test coverage (frac-0102b): `tests/test_render_pass.py` now includes `RenderPassEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/pass_.py` public surface through one register → enable → quantity → gate → apply lifecycle: a three-rule stack registered out of canonical order (`R3`, `R1`, `R2`) with `R1` quantity-disabled, `R2` carrying `quantities={"R2": 0.5}`, and `R3` role-gated by `frozenset({"melody", "bass"})` canonicalizes to `("R1", "R2", "R3")` with `effective_k` returning `0.0`/`0.5`/`1.0`; the first `apply(...)` returns a `PerformedPart` whose `applied_rules` skip the disabled `R1`, whose `quantities` record all three effective `k` values, and whose score-tree trace carries structurally correct `rule_id`/`k`/`roles` entries for `R2` (no role gate) and `R3` (forwarded role-gate frozenset); the second `apply(...)` with `quantity_overrides={"R1": 0.75}` re-enables `R1` so `applied_rules == ("R1", "R2", "R3")` in canonical order with the override `k=0.75` reflected in both `quantities` and the trace; and a combined diagnostic of rule order, effective-k map, and both performed-part snapshots (with `frozenset` role gates explicitly converted to sorted lists) round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_render_pass_depth.py` pins the render-pass test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4619 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:392:- Added depth-2 run_agent Ollama end-to-end test coverage (frac-0098): `tests/test_ollama_run_agent.py` now includes `OllamaRunAgentEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.run_agent` Ollama HTTP path through one happy lifecycle: `_invoke_ollama` is called once with the prompt, timeout, task category, and task label, the cloud subprocess invoker is fenced off, the pet manager records `start`/`end`/`idle` for `ollama` with a finite duration, the observatory records exactly one `gate_pass=True` task result alongside the `semaphore_acquired`/`semaphore_released` pair with no healing events, and the combined diagnostic round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_ollama_run_agent_depth.py` pins the run_agent test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `run_agent` behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4590 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:400:- Added depth-2 narrative API health end-to-end test coverage (frac-0094): `tests/test_narrative_api_health.py` now includes `NarrativeApiHealthEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `/health` HTTP surface through one cold healthy probe (auth-token-configured app, all checkers true, version `0.1.0`, world-store `list_events` probe call), one warm healthy probe (monotonic uptime, second probe call), one degraded probe (world store raises, ollama checker false, narrative engine importable), and a JSON-safe combined diagnostic round trip. `tests/test_test_narrative_api_health_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `cypherclaw.narrative_api.app` health behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4582 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
