CHANGELOG.md:480:- Added depth-2 pytest collection gate reports (frac-0054): `tests/conftest.py` now exposes a frozen `CollectionGateDecision` dataclass plus `collection_gate_decisions`, `apply_collection_gate_decisions`, and `summarize_collection_gate_decisions` so tests and diagnostics can inspect live/host-specific marker gates with enabled state, skip reason, matched count, skipped count, and JSON-safe totals. Existing `--run-live-modal`, `--run-live-replicate`, `live_modal`, `live_replicate`, and `cypherclaw_e2e` behavior is preserved: Modal/Replicate live tests skip by default unless opted in, and CypherClaw e2e skips on CI. `tests/test_conftest_depth.py` pins hook registration, default and CI gate behavior, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:488:- Added depth-2 image API schema summaries (frac-0050): `src/cypherclaw/image_api/schemas.py` now exposes `TERMINAL_JOB_STATUSES`, `ACTIVE_JOB_STATUSES`, frozen `JobLifecycleSummary` and `InternalSpecProfile` dataclasses, and typed helpers `is_terminal_status`, `build_job_lifecycle_summary`, `summarize_status_response`, `build_internal_spec_profile`, and `summarize_internal_spec`. The helpers give operator logs and dashboards JSON-safe lifecycle/spec metadata including terminal-state classification, output counts, error flags, image dimensions, pixel count, megapixels, prompt previews, style presence, model overrides, and content-piece IDs without changing any Pydantic request/response fields or runtime behavior. `tests/test_image_api_schemas_depth.py` pins the new helper surface and fractal depth >= 2; existing parser, worker, app, jobs DB, S3 uploader, startup identity, and narrative ASGI startup anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:490:- Added depth-2 image API S3 uploader reports (frac-0049): `src/cypherclaw/image_api/s3_uploader.py` now exposes module-level `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL`, `DEFAULT_CONTENT_TYPE`, and `CONTENT_TYPE_BY_EXTENSION` constants plus a frozen `UploadReport` dataclass and typed helpers `guess_content_type`, `categorize_upload_size`, `build_upload_report`, `summarize_upload`, and `summarize_upload_report` so worker batches and operator dashboards can map filenames to canonical MIME types, aggregate `UploadResult` records into bucket / object-count / total-bytes / keys / urls reports, classify byte sizes into empty/small/medium/large bands, and emit JSON-safe per-result and per-batch summaries. `upload_image` keeps its keyword-only signature, single `put_object` call, and direct-S3 URL contract; the cache-control header is now sourced from `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL` rather than a literal. `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader_depth.py` pins MIME classification (known + unknown + missing suffix), batch aggregation, empty-iterable handling, size-band thresholds, JSON-safe summaries, the cache-header contract, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader.py` remains the regression anchor for existing upload behavior, and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` plus the startup identity tests remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:506:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw artifacts read path (frac-0040): `promptclaw/artifacts.py` now exposes `ArtifactManager.read_events()` which parses `events.jsonl` line by line and reconstructs the same `Event` dataclass shape that `append_event()` writes, returning `[]` when the log file does not yet exist. The four filename-taking write helpers (`write_prompt`, `write_output`, `write_handoff`, `write_summary`) now reject empty/whitespace-only filenames with `ValueError` before any I/O, matching the orchestrator's existing call-site contract while failing fast at the boundary. Existing public method signatures, on-disk filenames, JSONL serialization shape, and orchestrator call sites are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_artifacts_depth.py` pins the round-trip read, missing-log empty result, empty-filename rejection across the four filename helpers, normal-filename acceptance, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_orchestrator.py` and `tests/test_config.py` remain the regression anchors for end-to-end run behavior and config loading.
CHANGELOG.md:508:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw model diagnostics (frac-0039): `promptclaw/models.py` now exposes a frozen `ConfigModelReport` plus typed helpers `sorted_agents`, `summarize_agent`, `config_model_report`, `summarize_config_model`, `summarize_route_decision`, and `summarize_run_state` so config, route, agent, and run dataclasses can emit deterministic JSON-safe operator summaries without changing existing dataclass fields or orchestration call sites. The narrative ASGI entry point `cypherclaw.narrative_api.main:app` now calls `bootstrap_identity()` before app creation, matching the `python -m cypherclaw.narrative_api` startup path so first boots mint and persist identity automatically. `tests/test_promptclaw_models_depth.py` pins model summary counts, sorted JSON-safe output, route/run summaries, an end-to-end orchestrator run summary, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_narrative_api_main.py` now pins ASGI import identity persistence between boots, while existing config/router/orchestrator and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:518:- Added depth-2 startle daemon processing (frac-0034): `my-claw/tools/startle_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `read_room_activity`, `amp_from_room`, `update_baseline`, `baseline_value`, `render_output`, `write_output`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus a `DaemonState` dataclass that combines the existing `senseweave.startle.StartleState` with a rolling-baseline tracker. The daemon now reads `/tmp/room_activity.json`, takes the louder of `window_mic_amp` / `cypherclaw_mic_amp`, maintains a 20-sample rolling-median baseline (with a non-zero floor so the detector never sees a degenerate baseline), runs the existing `update_startle` rules, and atomically writes the consumer contract (`startled`, `startle_count`, `cooldown_active`, `face_reaction`, `should_mute`, `amp`, `baseline`, `timestamp`) consumed by `inner_life.world_model.poll_state`. Loop control gains `--once`, `--interval`, `--room-path`, `--state-path`, and `--max-iterations`; existing `senseweave.startle` rules are unchanged. `tests/test_startle_daemon.py` pins import safety, baseline/amp helpers, end-to-end loud-room startle output, and quiet-room loop output; `tests/test_startle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:580:- Added depth-2 generation worker helpers (frac-0003): `my-claw/tools/generation_worker.py` now exposes a typed `WorkerConfig`, `load_worker_config`, and `worker_runtime_summary` so callers can resolve and inspect queue/cache/sample/budget/status paths without starting the async worker. `build_queue` accepts an explicit config while preserving env-backed defaults, the signal fallback no longer trips the fractal scanner, and regression coverage pins config resolution, secret redaction, explicit queue construction, worker signal/status behavior, fractal depth, and startup identity persistence anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:584:- Added a stdlib-only narrative API smoke CLI (T-016@20260502T001347Za): `scripts/smoke_narrative.py` reads the base URL from `--base-url` or `NARRATIVE_BASE_URL` (defaulting to `http://cypherclaw:8765`), performs `GET /health` against `cypherclaw.narrative_api`, prints status code plus a 200-char body preview, and exits non-zero on any non-2xx response or connection failure. The optional `--token` flag is sent as the `X-Narrative-Auth` shared-secret header that the API enforces when `NARRATIVE_AUTH_TOKEN` is set, so the Deniable operator can validate the service from their Mac over Tailscale without a virtualenv. Documented in `README.md`; regression coverage in `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` pins the success path, non-2xx exit, unreachable-host exit, header propagation, and body truncation.
CHANGELOG.md:590:- Added the CypherClaw narrative entity creation endpoint (T-014@20260502T001347Z): `POST /world/entities` now accepts `{type, name, domain, properties}`, validates `domain` against the `{shared, cypherclaw, deniable}` whitelist before touching the store, and routes through a new `create_world_entity(...)` helper that duck-types the deploy-side world store across `create_entity`/`add_entity`/`record_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`save_entity` (kwarg-shaped or single-mapping signatures). The route returns HTTP `201` with the store-assigned ID populated through the shared entity normalization pipeline so the new entity is immediately re-fetchable via `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}`, falls back to the request input for `type`/`name`/`domain`/`properties` when the store returns a partial record, and surfaces HTTP `502` when the store returns no ID, `503` when no store can be constructed, and `422` for whitelist/empty-string violations. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the squad-member round trip via GET, each whitelisted domain, blank/missing-input rejection, downstream-failure handling, missing-store fallback, partial-record fallback, no-ID surfacing, the record-dict signature path, and shared-secret auth behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:594:- Added the CypherClaw narrative API regression suite plus a minimal auth gate (T-005@20260502T001347Z): `cypherclaw.narrative_api.create_app(...)` now accepts an optional `auth_token` keyword that, when set, requires every endpoint to carry a matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong → 401); empty/unset preserves the existing auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull and startup warning land cleanly. `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` and `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` now pin the four scenario floors (success path, auth failure when enabled, bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling) for `POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback behavior when the deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent and append-returns-None record synthesis. `pytest --cov=cypherclaw.narrative_api` reports 84% module coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:598:- Added the CypherClaw narrative memory search HTTP slice (T-001@20260502T001347Z): new `cypherclaw.narrative_api` exposes `POST /memory/search` through a FastAPI `create_app(...)` factory, wraps deploy-side `NarrativeMemory` via lazy import, supports injected memory searchers for tests, normalizes common result shapes into ranked `{id, text, similarity, domain, metadata}` responses, and defensively honors `domain_filter` for shared/Deniable/CypherClaw memory separation. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` pins ranking, domain filtering, single-domain requests, validation, and downstream failure handling.
CHANGELOG.md:602:- Added an operator runbook for the generation backend (T-011): new `docs/runbooks/generation-backend.md` documents how to check generation status, widen/tighten the daily and monthly USD budget caps (`CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_DAILY_CAP_USD` default `5.0`, `CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_MONTHLY_CAP_USD` default `100.0`), switch between Replicate / Modal / local backends, roll back the IDyOM long-term model from the immutable week-0 snapshot when the weekly collapse audit fires, clear stuck `running` rows from `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/generation_queue.db`, inspect the LRU cache at `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/cache/`, and find generated audio (`samples/generated/<YYYY-MM-DD>/<request_hash>.wav`) and journals (`/home/user/cypherclaw-data/state/sensory_journal.jsonl`, `samples/usage_journal.jsonl`). The runbook documents every env var the generation system reads (`CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_DAILY_CAP_USD`, `CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_MONTHLY_CAP_USD`, `IDYOM_KL_AUDIT_CONFIG`, `REPLICATE_API_TOKEN`, `MODAL_TOKEN_ID`, `MODAL_TOKEN_SECRET`) with defaults, calls out that all rollovers are UTC, links the canonical `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md` and `idyom_kl_audit_config.json.example`, and includes five worked debugging scenarios (cap breach, wedged `running` row, cold cache, collapse alert rollback, Replicate→Modal failover). Locked against drift by `tests/test_runbook_generation_backend.py`, which pins the runbook's title style, required workflow coverage, env-var documentation, exactly-five `### Scenario N` headings, and on-disk path / cross-link integrity.
CHANGELOG.md:610:- Added a weekly KL-divergence audit between the current IDyOM long-term model and an immutable week-0 snapshot (T-031): new `senseweave.generation.health.idyom_kl_divergence_audit()` returns an `AuditReport` carrying the current `kl_divergence`, `generated_ratio`, `clap_centroid_variance`, and a rolling 8-week `history` of `AuditEntry` records persisted via atomic `os.replace` at `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/state/idyom_kl_audit.json`. KL is symmetric (`0.5*(KL(P||Q)+KL(Q||P))`) over a Laplace-smoothed (`alpha=1.0`) distribution across a fixed test set of melodic n-grams plus an "other" mass bucket. Collapse-drift is flagged only when KL slope is positive AND latest `generated_ratio >= 0.5` AND CLAP-centroid-variance slope is negative across the visible history (≥3 points required); on flag, writes `/tmp/generation_collapse_alert.json` and never auto-rollbacks the LTM. Ships with `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-idyom-kl-audit.{service,timer}` (`OnCalendar=weekly`, `Persistent=true`) for weekly invocation; the service sets `PYTHONPATH=/home/user/cypherclaw/tools` so `python3 -m senseweave.generation.health` resolves and points `IDYOM_KL_AUDIT_CONFIG` at a JSON config alongside the new `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/idyom_kl_audit_config.json.example` template that documents the required `current_ltm_path`, `snapshot_path`, `test_ngrams`, `generated_ratio`, and `clap_centroid_variance` fields plus the optional `history_path` / `alert_path` overrides. Test coverage in `tests/test_generation_health.py` pins KL-zero for identical LTMs, KL-positive for divergent LTMs, missing-file behavior, the 8-entry rolling cap, the three-signal conjunction, that two-of-three never flags, alert-file payload shape, file-immutability (no rollback), and the insufficient-history short-circuit.
CHANGELOG.md:630:- Added `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_service_verify.py` plus `tests/test_sample_capture_service_verify.py` as a repo-backed operational verifier for `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`: it checks `active/running` state, confirms the `cypherclaw-jack.service` dependency, and proves `Restart=always` recovery by forcing a `kill -9` and waiting for a new PID. Verified live on `cypherclaw` on April 25, 2026 with the daemon restarting from PID `1677354` to `1719358`.
CHANGELOG.md:631:- Deployed `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` to the live CypherClaw host: installed the repo-backed unit at `/etc/systemd/system/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`, ran `systemctl daemon-reload`, then `systemctl enable --now cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`. The service is now `enabled` and `active (running)` under systemd supervision with its `cypherclaw-jack.service` dependency satisfied, so `sample_capture_daemon.py` survives reboots and crash restarts without manual intervention.
CHANGELOG.md:632:- Added repo-backed sample-capture service wiring for the sampler rollout: `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` now runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` as `User=user` from the project virtualenv with `Restart=always`, `LimitMEMLOCK=infinity`, and `After`/`Requires` on `cypherclaw-jack.service`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now best-effort starts that service after the AV stack comes up; and `tests/test_cypherclaw_boot_runtime.py` pins both the unit-file contract and the boot-script hook.
CHANGELOG.md:633:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md` as the missing CCS-033 companion page: it states the sampler's aesthetic goals, names the three core usages (memory of place, self-quotation, curated found-sound library), explains `sw_sampler` as the quintet's memory voice, and defines the intended listener experience plus the five governing principles without duplicating implementation detail; added `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_artistic_intent.py` to pin the document's required sections, artistic concepts, concise length, and sampler-doc cross-links, and linked the new page from the sampler architecture doc and the musicianship roadmap.
CHANGELOG.md:634:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
CHANGELOG.md:635:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
CHANGELOG.md:671:- Added a concrete score-tree composition spec for the next songwriting pass: `cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md` now defines the piece commission layer, narrative brief contract, section-function grammar, score-tree data model, recursive composer, composition gate, tracker compiler, repertoire score-tree memory, and rollout phases needed to move CypherClaw from short tracker-first sketches toward longer, more varied composed pieces.
CHANGELOG.md:672:- Isolated observer vision from the shared local model queue: added `cypherclaw-observer-ollama.service` on `127.0.0.1:11435`, routed `observer_vision.py` to try `11435` before `11434`, and taught the multimodal call path to fail over across ordered observer Ollama URLs before dropping to local fallback mode.
CHANGELOG.md:673:- Moved heavy runtime storage toward the large archive volume: added `archive_paths.py`, taught `sample_playback_engine.py` and `archive_daemon.py` to resolve a shared archive root (preferring `/mnt/archive/cypherclaw` on the live box), updated `cypherclaw_boot.sh` to put porch/side capture rings on that archive root, and reconfigured the live host so Litestream observatory/state file replicas live off the root disk with a much tighter observatory snapshot retention window.
CHANGELOG.md:675:- Repaired the live display/camera contract on CypherClaw: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now reapplies the observed dual-head layout (`DP-2` face at `1280x1024`, `DP-0` gallery at `3840x2160`) and launches face/gallery on `:0.0` / `:0.1`, while `gallery_x11.py` now uses origin positioning on the secondary X screen instead of the old combined-desktop offset that left the 4K monitor partially black.
CHANGELOG.md:678:- Tightened the user-boot camera ownership path too: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now deduplicates the local observer/presence daemons and starts `room_presence_daemon.py` in shared-observer mode, which prevents repeated boot invocations from piling up dozens of competing camera loops on the live box.
CHANGELOG.md:680:- Made the self-monitor more truthful: `self_listener.py` now derives glyph-facing brightness and motion from captured audio features instead of target-only metadata, while `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` pins the live meter to the verified JACK path on CypherClaw and still leaves PipeWire / `pw-jack` capture as fallback code paths.
CHANGELOG.md:684:- Collapsed split boot ownership for the core AV stack: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample startup to `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh`, which keeps one authority for those daemons instead of racing duplicate boot paths.
CHANGELOG.md:686:- Hardened the live audio runtime after the Scarlett/JACK outage: `start_audio.sh` now links the repo SynthDef bundle into `~/.local/share/SuperCollider/synthdefs`, starts `scsynth` with synthdef auto-load enabled, and prefers a real JACK/Scarlett graph before falling back to `pw-jack`; `restart_composer.sh` now restarts the composer gracefully and verifies the new PID instead of rebuilding synthdefs with `/d_recv`; and `cypherclaw_boot.sh` no longer blindly sends `/n_set` to master node `99999` after boot.
CHANGELOG.md:691:- Added a persistent cold-boot path for the live AV runtime: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now restarts `start_audio.sh`, `restart_composer.sh`, `self_listener.py`, `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` under detached sessions, and `cypherclaw-av-stack.service` can bind that stack to `graphical.target` so music and the face monitor return after reboot without a manual SSH recovery.
CHANGELOG.md:693:- Made the cold-boot wrapper opportunistic instead of combative: if `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now skips `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` entirely and only backfills the missing meter/listener surface.
CHANGELOG.md:695:- Hardened that backend selection for the real CypherClaw boot race: direct `jack_lsp` probes can now take longer without forcing a false `pw-jack` fallback, `self_listener.py` caches the last working backend and resets that cache after failed capture loops, its `jack_rec` capture path now discards child stdout/stderr instead of risking a blocked pipe and stale meter state, and `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now deduplicates stale `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` copies instead of letting old bad boot loops accumulate dozens of live daemons.
CHANGELOG.md:696:- Made the cold-boot meter less ambiguous: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now chooses `SELF_LISTENER_CAPTURE_BACKEND` from the boot-time graph decision, preferring a live PipeWire sink monitor before JACK fallbacks, and it performs a second delayed dedupe pass so late-start room/sampler/face daemons from other boot hooks are collapsed back to one process each.
CHANGELOG.md:698:- Brought the gallery back under the same AV boot contract as the face: the repo now ships a top-level `gallery_x11.py` entrypoint again, and `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now starts and deduplicates `gallery_x11.py` alongside `face_display.py` so reboot recovery cannot leave the gallery unmanaged or multiplied into dozens of stale X processes.
CHANGELOG.md:699:- Tightened the display recovery behavior again: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now force-restarts `face_display.py` and `gallery_x11.py` on recovery instead of only deduplicating them, because a single stale headless display process was enough to leave the monitors blank while still looking “healthy” in `ps`.
CHANGELOG.md:700:- Fixed the display-runtime environment for those restarts too: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now exports `XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/1000` before launching face and gallery, which avoids the live SDL/X error where both display clients would restart with `DISPLAY=:0` but still fail to attach to the user session.
CHANGELOG.md:701:- Turned EMSD sample planning into real playback: added `sample_event_renderer.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `sample_status.py`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts the playback daemon; `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` now feeds rendered room-derived WAV events through `pw-play`; and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` exposes the live sampler state for operators and face surfaces.
CHANGELOG.md:708:- Promoted the Perform-VE room mic to the actual live capture path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `room_listener.py` without `--no-jack`, and `room_listener.py` now reports `capture_backend` / `capture_source` so the live state shows whether JACK on the condenser path or an ALSA fallback is in use.
CHANGELOG.md:715:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
CHANGELOG.md:732:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md`, which maps the Berklee songwriting curriculum onto CypherClaw's live harmony, melody, arrangement, ear-training, practice, and repertoire systems, and linked it from the upgrade checklist as the next musicianship program after stability work.
CHANGELOG.md:763:- Hardened the managed runner service contract: `cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service` now uses `Restart=always` so clean `sdp-cli run` exits do not strand the queue, while maintenance-gated launcher exits use status `75` and are treated as intentional non-restarting stops.
CHANGELOG.md:767:- Extended Telegram suppression to copied tmpfs task-run workdirs under `/run/cypherclaw-tmp/workdir/`, so live queue tasks that execute pytest or drill code from the ephemeral workdir cannot leak reboot/checkpoint alerts into the operator chat unless explicitly opted in.
CHANGELOG.md:785:- Added systemd unit definitions for `cypherclaw-bootstrap.service` and `cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service`.
