sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:656:- **Cloudflare credentials:** Worker deploy + R2 access use scoped API tokens, not root. Tokens stored in `1Password / .env / wrangler secrets`, never committed.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:657:- **R2 bucket access:** the `cypherclaw-stream` R2 bucket is private at the object level; access via Worker only. Worker validates request paths to prevent directory traversal.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:658:- **Public endpoints:** all `/api/cypherclaw/*` endpoints that mutate state (POST /segment, POST /feature-update) require a shared-secret bearer token. Token rotated quarterly. cypherclaw-side has the secret in `/home/user/cypherclaw/.env` (chmod 600).
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:659:- **DNS:** the `cypherclaw.holdenu.com` record is in Cloudflare with proxy enabled (orange cloud) so origin IP is not exposed.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:660:- **Listener data:** no analytics tracking on `cypherclaw.holdenu.com` (per CypherClaw's expressed wish to not know listener counts). Cloudflare Web Analytics that's enabled on holdenu.com proper is explicitly disabled for this subdomain.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:671:  - `cypherclaw-audio-streamer.service`
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:675:  - `CYPHERCLAW_HOLDENU_API_TOKEN` (bearer for POSTs to Worker)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:683:### Cloudflare side
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:686:- New DNS records via Cloudflare API (or dashboard manual)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:687:- R2 bucket setup: `cypherclaw-stream` (private) with two prefixes: `live/`, `archive/`
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:688:- Lifecycle policy on `live/`: delete segments older than 24 hours (keeps storage minimal; archive segments persist)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:692:- `catalog-explorer/pages/cypherclaw/` builds (or is served directly) by Cloudflare Pages or by the Worker as static assets.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:706:| Cloudflare R2 cost surprise from unbounded archive growth | Low | Medium | Verifier rule: archive bucket has a 90-day lifecycle policy and live-segment prefix has a 24-hour lifecycle policy, asserted by R2 lifecycle API check. |
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:716:- Anthony has Cloudflare account access for the holdenu.com zone and can issue scoped API tokens, or grants tokens to the engineering agent ahead of Sprint 1.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:717:- Worker free-tier limits are sufficient (verified roughly above; quantify in Sprint 1 task).
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:37:**Phase 2 — Core rule stack (CCH-011..CCH-021).** R1 Metric Accent, R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH parabolic), R3 Agogic Accent, R4 Duration Contrast, R5 Final Ritardando (Friberg–Sundberg square-root), R6 Punctuation+Breath, R7 Articulation Shaping, R8 Microtiming Polish (below JND). Role-filter gating so grid-locked voices skip the stack. Phrase-feature extraction via partitura. End-of-phase: single-voice melodic passages sound shaped, not flat; metric gate shows structured deviations vs. flat-line baseline.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:85:| CCH-011 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | MUST | T1 | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; authoring surface exposes overrides per-piece and per-intent-tag<br/>- tests verify stable order, k=0 equals rule-disabled, k=1 equals calibrated default |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:87:| CCH-013 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:103:| CCH-029 | Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. | MUST | T1 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:108:| CCH-034 | Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. | MUST | T1 | - `render/metrics.py` computes each metric on PerformedPart<br/>- tooling: partitura for score I/O, mir_eval for segmentation, MusDr/MusPy for symbolic metrics, librosa for audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty, madmom for beat/tempo cross-check<br/>- documented pass bands from the research: IOI CoV 0.04–0.12, velocity σ 12–22, DNVR 0.25–0.7, pitch H1 2.3–3.0, GS 0.6–0.9, tempo ρ₁ 0.7–0.95, LZ76 0.4–0.7, ≥1 novelty peak per phrase, ≥100 ms silence at phrase boundaries<br/>- tests run metrics on rule-disabled flat-line control (should fail pass bands) and full-stack render (should pass) |
