sdp/verification/t-033@20260425t183959z-verify.md:44:One behavior worth noting for future reference: files that match multiple category buckets in `anthony-library.toml` (e.g., a file named `bass drum loop.wav` matching both the drums and bass patterns) will be imported once per matching bucket with `INSERT OR REPLACE`, resulting in the tags from the last matching bucket winning. This is acceptable for the current migration — all 101 final records have non-empty tags — but a future improvement could union tags across all matching buckets rather than replacing.
