     1	# Task T-025 Specification: CypherClaw Segment Ingest Worker
     2	
     3	## Problem Statement
     4	
     5	CypherClaw's live audio streamer produces short Ogg/Opus segment files, but the
     6	Cloudflare Worker has no CypherClaw ingest route yet. T-025 adds the first
     7	Worker-side live stream primitive: authenticated `POST /api/cypherclaw/segment`
     8	requests must store one binary segment in the existing R2 media bucket so later
     9	tasks can build HLS playlist serving and public playback.
    10	
    11	## Technical Approach
    12	
    13	- Extend the existing `catalog-explorer/worker/src/index.ts` Cloudflare Worker.
    14	- Reuse the existing `MEDIA` R2 binding; no new bucket or dependency is needed.
    15	- Follow the existing write-endpoint pattern and require
    16	  `Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_TOKEN>` before storing a segment.
    17	- Accept a binary request body with metadata headers:
    18	  - `X-CypherClaw-Sequence` required, non-negative integer.
    19	  - `X-CypherClaw-Captured-At` optional ISO timestamp; defaults to Worker time.
    20	  - `X-CypherClaw-Duration`, `X-CypherClaw-Scene`, and
    21	    `X-CypherClaw-Tuning` optional metadata.
    22	- Store objects at `cypherclaw/live/{YYYY-MM-DD}/seg-{sequence}.opus`.
    23	- Preserve content type from `Content-Type`, defaulting to
    24	  `audio/ogg; codecs=opus`.
    25	- Return JSON with `ok`, `key`, `size`, `etag`, and normalized `sequence`.
    26	
    27	## Edge Cases
    28	
    29	- Missing or incorrect bearer token returns `401` and does not write to R2.
    30	- Missing body returns `400`.
    31	- Missing, negative, or non-integer sequence returns `400`.
    32	- Invalid `X-CypherClaw-Captured-At` returns `400`.
    33	- Optional scene and tuning metadata are sanitized by Cloudflare R2 metadata
    34	  storage as simple strings only.
    35	- This task does not build playlist generation, public segment serving, DNS,
    36	  TLS, or the streamer POST client; those are later PRD tasks.
    37	- The generated startup identity hardening bullets are already covered by the
    38	  existing PromptClaw startup identity anchors. T-025 does not change startup
    39	  flow; it will re-run those anchors as regression verification.
    40	
    41	## Acceptance Criteria
    42	
    43	1. Authenticated `POST /api/cypherclaw/segment` writes the request body to R2 at
    44	   the canonical live segment key and the object is visible via R2 listing.
    45	   VERIFY:
